headline: Texas Instruments (TXN) Earnings Rebound Challenges Bearish Margin Narratives
summary: Texas Instruments (TXN) turned in a 1.7% year-over-year increase in earnings, outpacing its five-year average decline of 5.9% per year. While net profit margins narrowed to 29.1% from last year's 31.4%, investors are eyeing a forecasted 8.3% annual revenue growth and 12.9% annual earnings growth in the years ahead, both trailing the broader US market's expectations.
